On Wed, 23 Apr 2008, Jeremiah Stutte wrote:

> the turn signal is brand new.  the old dimmer relay has no numbers
> stamped on it just says bergson and ind. brassialle.  both relays are
> five prong and have stamped on the bottom next to each prong the same
> numbers.  the new relay also has the code DNI 0127 on the case body.
> brazilian made, also.

> should i check were the wires come into the steering column?  what
> would i look for?

Given your symptoms, I'd suspect a bad ground to the dimmer contact on the
turn signal switch.  I recall I had to repair this on my bus when the
dimmer went intermittant.  It's pretty obvious when you disassemble the
turn signal switch.

George
